"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code is incorrectly using both `ax.set_xticks()` and `ax.xaxis.set_major_locator()`. `ax.set_xticks()` is used to manually set the x-axis tick locations, while `ax.xaxis.set_major_locator()` is used to automatically set the major tick locations. Using both can cause conflicts and lead to unexpected results.\",\n  \"patch\": \"17,18c17\\n< ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n< ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n---\\n> # Removed manual tick setting to avoid conflict with MonthLocator\\n\"\n}"